South Africa May Issue a $126 Billion Nuclear Plant Tender, M&G Reports

-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 
2011-10-07T05:00:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-07/south-africa-may-issue-a-126-billion-nuclear-plant-tender-m-g-reports.html
South Africa  may issue a 1 trillion
rand ($126 billion) tender for the construction of six nuclear
plants by 2030, Johannesburg’s Mail & Guardian newspaper said,
citing unidentified people in government and the industry.  The country’s Department of Energy submitted its proposal
to the Cabinet last month, the newspaper said.  French and Chinese companies may prepare a joint bid, the
Mail & Guardian said, citing the people. It listed the potential
bidders as Areva SA,  EDF SA (EDF) ,  Toshiba Corp. (6502) ’s  Westinghouse
ELectric Corp., China Guangdong Nuclear Power Holding Corp.,
 Korea Electric Power Corp. (KEP)  and Rosatom Corp.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  